---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";
---
<Base
  title="Coverage map"
  description="Where PalmasMesh reaches across Palmas del Mar. A live coverage map is on the way — here's the picture for now."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="The network"
    title="Where the mesh reaches"
    lede="As more neighbors join and more nodes go up around Palmas, our coverage grows. A live map is in the works — here's where things stand."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="map-placeholder" role="img" aria-label="Placeholder illustration of the PalmasMesh coverage area around Palmas del Mar. A detailed live map is coming soon.">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 800 420" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid slice" aria-hidden="true">
          <defs>
            <radialGradient id="cov" cx="50%" cy="45%" r="55%">
              <stop offset="0%" stop-color="rgba(255,179,71,0.28)"/>
              <stop offset="60%" stop-color="rgba(47,182,163,0.12)"/>
              <stop offset="100%" stop-color="rgba(47,182,163,0)"/>
            </radialGradient>
          </defs>
          <rect width="800" height="420" fill="#0f2233"/>
          <!-- coastline suggestion -->
          <path d="M0 300 Q 200 260 380 300 T 800 280 V420 H0 Z" fill="#0a1622" opacity="0.7"/>
          <!-- coverage glow -->
          <circle cx="400" cy="200" r="220" fill="url(#cov)"/>
          <!-- nodes + links -->
          <g stroke="#9fb6c0" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.55">
            <line x1="400" y1="200" x2="270" y2="150"/>
            <line x1="400" y1="200" x2="540" y2="160"/>
            <line x1="270" y1="150" x2="540" y2="160"/>
          </g>
          <g>
            <circle cx="400" cy="200" r="9" fill="#ffb347"/>
            <circle cx="270" cy="150" r="7" fill="#2fb6a3"/>
            <circle cx="540" cy="160" r="7" fill="#2fb6a3"/>
          </g>
          <text x="400" y="240" text-anchor="middle" fill="#9fb6c0" font-family="monospace" font-size="15" letter-spacing="2">PALMAS DEL MAR</text>
        </svg>
        <div class="map-badge">
          <span class="pill">⬤ Live map coming soon</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="map-context wrap-narrow">
        <h2>What you're looking at</h2>
        <p>
          PalmasMesh is up and running with rooftop nodes inside Palmas del Mar,
          and we're steadily adding coverage as neighbors join and as we link up
          with other mesh nodes across eastern Puerto Rico — even into Vieques,
          Culebra and the USVI.
        </p>
        <p>
          We're building a proper interactive map that shows live nodes and the
          real coverage area. For now, the short version: if you're in Palmas
          del Mar, there's a good chance you're already within reach — and every
          new node anyone adds extends it a little further.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Want to help fill in the map?</strong> Hosting a node on a
          roof, balcony, or window — especially up high — is the single best way
          to grow coverage for everyone. If you've got a good spot, <a href="/contact/">we'd love to
          talk</a>.
        </p>
        <div class="next-row">
          <a href="/hardware/" class="btn btn-primary">Get a node going →</a>
          <a href="/faq/" class="btn btn-dark">How far does it reach?</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .map-placeholder {
      position: relative;
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      aspect-ratio: 800 / 420;
      background: #0f2233;
    }
    .map-placeholder svg { display: block; width: 100%; height: 100%; }
    .map-badge {
      position: absolute;
      top: 1rem; left: 1rem;
    }
    .map-context { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
    .next-row { display: flex; gap: 0.8rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  </style>
</Base>
